value.value: An atmospheric wind which 1) has an increased rate relative to other winds in the same region and 2) is followed by a lull.

According to U.S. weather observing practice, gusts are reported when the peak wind speed reaches at least 16 knots and the variation in wind speed between the peaks and lulls is at least 9 knots. The duration of a gust is usually less than 20 seconds.

label.value: concentration of carbon dioxide in an atmosphere

definition.value: The concentration of carbon dioxide when measured in air that is part of an atmosphere.
